Singer Timi Dakolo has explained why he’ll gladly sing at any political event ahead of the 2023 elections. Following his performance at the presidential declaration of former Vice President Atiku Abubakar, Dakolo has continued to receive bashing from some social media users who interpreted his move as an endorsement for the PDP presidential candidate. Atiku officially declared his intention to contest in the 2023 presidential election at the international conference centre (ICC) in Abuja on Wednesday, March 23. At the event, Dakolo thrilled guests with a beautiful performance of ‘Great Nation’, his hit song.   Gideon Okeke calls out filmmaker Frank Rajah over alleged…     Filmmaker Moses Ebere dies     Cuppy reacts after Twitter user tells her to get pregnant   The former vice-president also took to his Twitter page to share a video clip of Dakolo’s performance, referring to his hit song as ‘Unity Song.’ Reacting to social media’s provocation of his performance at the presidential declaration event hosted by Atiku, the 41-year-old singer justified his action. Dakolo insisted he will go to any such event to do what he does best to guarantee his daily bread. “I will sing and collect bread my Guy, if it pains you well well, go sing your own,” he wrote.